    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"thumbs up\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"thumbs up\">:thumbs_up:</span> cfallin submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13953#pullrequestreview-4773616001\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thanks! Happy to merge once the rustfmt issue is fixed.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 612578178,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1784899835
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13953#issuecomment-5070514884\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13953\">PR #13953</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>One possible note here is that this is an intentional idiom you'll find throughout Wasmtime in a number of places. The intentional part is that if a new variant is added the compiler's exhaustive-match checks flag the <code>match</code> as \"gotta add more arms here\". With a catch-all like proposed in this PR adding a new variant will get no such warnings and it'd be some bug later own down the road to force adding the <code>match</code>. Personally I find that more valuable than removing lines, but that's also a subjective call </p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 612580575,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1784900581
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"cross mark\" class=\"emoji emoji-274c\" role=\"img\" title=\"cross mark\">:cross_mark:</span> cfallin closed without merge <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13953\">PR #13953</a>.</p>",
        "id": 612585958,
